Bone marrow: please pool according to PI's instructions for FACS.
 All other tissues: Please collect "paired" samples from all tissues, 1 sample to be fixed in 10%NBF, 1 sample frozen in OCT. For pinnas: please remove at base, split in half along longitudinal axis (tip to base) embed one half "on edge" in OCT, one half in 10% NBF (4 samples total, left and right). For skin: use matched area dorsal between shoulder blades for all animals. OCT samples embed on edge. For spleen: Transverse dissection into 4 blocks. Embed 2 in OCT (2 blocks) and 2 in 10% NBF (1 block). For jejunum: Collect 8 transverse segments approximately 4 mm long, embed 4 in OCT (4 blocks) and 4 in 10% NBF (1 block).
